<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Matus</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Guzman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation—Handed to the
                                Secretary of State by the Nicaraguan minister, April 23, 1895, 3
                                p.m.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-23"><hi rend="italic">April 23,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Our representative at London cables British Government will not accede to
                            our request. Ultimatum will be notified to-day.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>